From: Hybrid Token-Efficient Routing Agent
Date: 2026
Subject: Per-task timeout + type-aware routing (daemon-thread-based)

Replace ThreadPoolExecutor with a plain threading.Thread(daemon=True)
to fix a critical atexit-blocking flaw:

- concurrent.futures registers an atexit handler that waits for ALL pool
  threads to finish before the process can exit — meaning an abandoned,
  still-running generate() call would silently block container shutdown
  until it finished, defeating the timeout entirely.
- Daemon threads are killed automatically by the interpreter at process
  exit with zero waiting. No atexit hook, no blocking.

Implementation uses a shared Event (set by the worker when done) and a
single-item result container. The main thread waits on Event.wait(timeout=...)
and never calls .join() on the background thread.

Structure:
1. Module-level daemon Thread + Event + result container.
2. _run_local_with_timeout() checks is_alive() before starting a new call.
3. On timeout, returns None — the daemon thread is abandoned and will be
   killed automatically at process exit.
4. Per-task-type timeouts via dict (math=90s, factual_qa=30s, others=45s).
5. slow_task_types skips local entirely for known-slow task types.

